&quot;CH on %t&quot; <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=161363><img src=http://www.strike9.com/file.aspx/path=/aamedorpo/fullsize/showsig.jpg border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uammelen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 251<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 2:13:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 10k hp tanks</span><hr size=1> You haven't remained at the same effectiveness since Kunark.  You're more effective now because of increased hp on the people you are healing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucerosofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceros of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 880<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 2:35:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 10k hp tanks</span><hr size=1> Well, you know, not all cleric cheal chains are totally mindless.<br>
<br>
Maybe that's the difference between a great guild and a good guild or a zerg guild.  Well, one of them, at least. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=saalron>Saalron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 596<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 2:54:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ahem</span><hr size=1> I think a few people mistook what I wrote. Cheal is not something I have a personal grudge against. It's an amazing spell, etc.<br>
<br>
The problem with cheal is this: it's mana/hp ratio will continually improve as the game grows. You can't balance spells out and balance encounters out properly when the thing you are balancing against is constantly increasing unless you create mobs who are also constantly increasing in effectiveness or zones that are always growing in difficulty. Cheal + time = work for verant.<br>
<br>
As the game gets older, if cheal remains (and it will because the retooling you would have to do if you removed it is basically 2 full expansions), you will see other healing spells created to keep druids and shaman from being laughable because cheal can now heal for it's full amount as mudflation has given tanks 10k hp.<br>
<br>
It's not a bitch from me tho, Baps. It's just the state of the game. Velious and Luclin would not be what they were if there was no cheal so it's not really possible to say what the state of the game would be if it never existed.<br>
<br>
The only way to make cheal slide back into balance without having to revamp the whole damn game is to assign it's mana cost based on the hit points it heals. Find the best other ratio heal spell in the game (is it torpor ?) and then give cheal the same cost ratio, maybe 25% of a better ratio since it's so definitive, and then put in a class aa for clerics to make it a smidgeon better.<br>
<br>
That, or just hope that the eq2 spell engine doesn't have preset ratios in the form of spells that will become obsolete because of mudflation. Instead, define spellcost as a ratio to hit points healed (or nuked for), with multipliers for casting time, recast time, and reagent usage and let players decide how to make the spells they want to use. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uanikacrystalwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Anika Crystalwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Admin Gnome</span><br>  Posts: 1151<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 3:13:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=29>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 10k hp tanks</span><hr size=1> Baldrik is right, there's a huge difference between a CHeal chain and a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> good</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> CHeal chain.  Smacking a button every 12 seconds is the ideal scenario, but there's a LOT of external influences that can throw wrenches into that perfect world, and learning to adapt on-the-fly takes practice.  6 months ago, PO's CHeal chains were pathetic as well - just like anything, keeping a tank up takes practice.<br>
<br>
That said though, let's take a look at Balance.  Yes, it turns CHeal into a 2500 HP heal, problem is, it cuts all our other heals by 75% as well, meaning CHeal is the ONLY spell that's useable.  Yes, they've ended up reducing it's effectiveness in that encounter, but as a result they've increased the need to use CHeal.  <br>
<br>
The problem with CHeal is that at L39, clerics get 'the' end-game heal.  There is nothing in my full spellbook that even comes *close* to healing 10k HP.  The next closest spot heal?  Divine Light, which is a base heal of 955 HP.  Sure, with AA skills and focus items, I can get that up to 1200-1300, but it costs 350 mana to cast.  CHeal costs 400 mana.  Why even bother?  For 50 more mana I can heal 10 times as many HP.  Verant made a 10K heal appear too early in the game, and cost too little mana to cast.  Unfortunately, they can't change it now, or they have to reture the entire game.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uammelen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 252<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 3:30:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 10k hp tanks</span><hr size=1> I guess I see the point in griping about cheal being lvl 39.<br>
<br>
Maybe they could move cheal to lvl 59 or something, and make a lvl 39 spell that is a 10s cast 2k hp heal for 400 mana or something, then clerics would not feel their endgame spell was at 39.<br>
<br>
However, what happens pre 60 has little if any impact on any of us anymore, since those days are so far in the past and it's hard to remember what it was like to be 39.<br>
<br>
At 39, I do remember that relatively few clerics even used cheal, because often tanks had 1kish hp and it just wasn't efficient compared to sup heal. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uammelen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ammelen</A> at: 8/9/02 4:06:03 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucerosofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceros of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 882<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 3:38:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 10k hp tanks</span><hr size=1> I don't think that cheal was introduced too early.  It's not like it gives massive advantages to a 39 cleric. <br>
<br>
cheal is a self scaling spell.  It becomes more efficient and useful over time.  I really don't believe that it's massively unbalanced.  Its effectiveness is limited by the manapool of the cleric and the hitpoints of the tank. <br>
<br>
When a major equipment upgrade occurs in the game, cheal is also upgraded.  Major equipment upgrades tend to occur during expansions when other spell lines are upgraded, so it's not a huge deal, especially because encounters are designed with cheal in mind.<br>
<br>
It's not like you can stick a level 39 cleric in VT to replace a level 60 cleric. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umeiren.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meiren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 575<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 3:53:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 10k hp tanks</span><hr size=1> Just want to say, that CHeal can not, in any way, be unbalancing to the game.<br>
<br>
Simply because the game is balanced around cheal, in regards to end game content.<br>
<br>
Lushe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/utropicsdelight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TropicsDelight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 968<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 4:04:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 10k hp tanks</span><hr size=1> Complete heal is the most retarded thing that ever came into the game of EQ, well maybe one of them there are alot of contenders Verant has put in.<br>
<br>
You say you like CH chains and they make fights a challange? Bah, CH chains take no more challange then a well planned encounter where spot heals would be better. You say spamming the warrior with spot heals takes less skill? Well yeah but in a good encounter not only the warrior is going to be getting hit, creatures all over the place, rampage, the inability to break areas and fight mobs single all would make the game difficult while not relying on a CH chain. Tanks with 6500+ HPS, CH, Mobs hitting for 1000+, AC caps, No true damage mitigation for true tank classes, ect.... all screwed up EQ. A fight with spots is difficult if multiple things are happening at one time and many people are getting hit and gaining/losing agro. The only way CH chains are tougher then spamming spots are in a single mob fight where a single person has the agro and the mob has the power to kill the tank in 2 rounds.<br>
<br>
Honestly, a fight with CH chains and a single tank is the most boring bloody thing in EQ and it is the predominate way things are done in most fights. Every fight is pretty much the same no matter what mob you are fighting (ok a couple mobs in Ssra might be different, maybe VT). You set the CH chain to cast every 2 seconds, 3 seconds, 4 seconds, whatever and you get the tank in there and then the fight is pretty much staying awake and clicking your button at the correct time. This is the most lame strategical system a RPG could ever come up with. A cleric does not have to watch a fight, all they need to see is the chat box to know when to cast that next CH, they dont need actual graphic pictures on the screen at all.<br>
