Honestly, there is no game there. Fights have been broken down into mathimatical formulas where there is NO actual need for thought. A computer program could do the job of the best cleric in the game better then he himself could. The healing structure of this game take no ability to think or analize a situation or improvize, just pure timing of clicking buttons. If you think that is a good thing then I am not sure what to say.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uammelen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 253<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 4:13:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 10k hp tanks</span><hr size=1> Tropics, the eq you envision is one without much variation in roles between classes.  I like the fact that classes have to do very different and specific things, like tanking.  I would not want to see mobs running aorund hitting everyone as clerics all just spam spot heals on the various people getting hit.  Complete heal allows for a huge upgrade in efficiency, the price you pay is a need to coordinate cheals in advance, to time it all precisely, to react extremely quickly if things go wrong.  This separates the good guilds from the bad ones.  It provides the challenge in the game.  Any cleric can just watch th 6 hp bars in his group and as oon as one drops to 1 bubble target and spam a heal, but God would that be boring.<br>
<br>
I love the model of controlling and focusing aggro, and eq is designed around that, and it has made eq very successful.  It gives the different classes discrete roles.<br>
<br>
I entirely agree with Ceros, complete heal, though introduced at lvl 39, is not very useful then.  It self scales as the cleric levels and as expansions are released.<br>
<br>
Ammelen <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ucerosofvazaelle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ceros of Vazaelle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 883<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 4:18:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 10k hp tanks</span><hr size=1> I suspect that most people believe that a skilled cheal chain is of no benefit have never been in a very good guild.  I'm not trying to talk trash, but..<br>
<br>
